WEBVTT

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.800
( waves lapping )

00:00:10.800 --> 00:00:12.933
Fujimaki: YOU'D LIKE THAT,
WOULDN'T YOU?

00:00:12.933 --> 00:00:14.500
I SUPPOSE SOME SCORPIONS

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.833
WOULD RATHER SHUT THEIR EYES
TO THEIR TRUE NATURE

00:00:16.833 --> 00:00:19.933
AND BE POISONED BY THE VENOM
OF THEIR OWN DREAMS.

00:00:19.933 --> 00:00:22.333
SORRY, COACH NANBU,

00:00:22.333 --> 00:00:25.200
BUT THIS IS THE END OF THE RIDE.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:26.800
Nanbu: PLEASE, CAN'T WE JUST‐‐

00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:29.200
Fujimaki: YOU'RE GONNA
TELL HIM EVERYTHING.

00:00:32.166 --> 00:00:33.633
Joe: TALK ABOUT IMPATIENT.

00:00:33.633 --> 00:00:36.000
ALREADY HERE
TO CLAIM THE PRIZE MONEY?

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.466
Nanbu: J‐JOE.

00:00:40.966 --> 00:00:42.100
( zipper zips )

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:43.233
‐ ( splashing )
‐ Joe: DAMN.

00:00:43.233 --> 00:00:44.900
STILL PISSING BLOOD.

00:00:44.900 --> 00:00:46.133
( Nanbu groans )

00:00:47.766 --> 00:00:48.500
( match strikes )

00:00:50.933 --> 00:00:52.700
JOE, YOU SEE, THE TRUTH IS‐‐

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.100
Joe: JUST TELL HIM, POPS.

00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:57.166
IT'S TOO EARLY
TO CELEBRATE, ISN'T IT?

00:00:57.166 --> 00:00:58.833
THE REAL FIGHT STARTS
AS SOON AS WE‐‐

00:00:58.833 --> 00:01:01.273
Nanbu: THERE'S NOT
GONNA BE A REAL FIGHT!

00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:03.273
Sachio: HMM?

00:01:07.906 --> 00:01:09.673
♪

00:01:20.973 --> 00:01:22.673
( singing in Japanese )

00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:43.213
Nanbu: I KNOW
HOW TO HANDLE THINGS.

00:02:43.213 --> 00:02:45.980
I'VE BEEN BETTING ON BLUFFS
MY WHOLE DAMN LIFE!

00:02:45.980 --> 00:02:47.513
SO, "WHAT CAN FRAUDS DO?"

00:02:47.513 --> 00:02:50.313
I'M GONNA SHOW YOU
EXACTLY WHAT WE CAN DO!

00:02:52.946 --> 00:02:55.513
Fujimaki: HMPH. NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

00:02:55.513 --> 00:02:57.180
‐ ( Nanbu gasps )
‐ Fujimaki: I DON'T WANT TO HEAR

00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:00.446
THE DESPERATE RAMBLINGS
OF A DREAMER CHASING A FANTASY.

00:03:00.446 --> 00:03:03.620
I WANT AN ANSWER
FROM THE REAL YOU.

00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:06.486
YES, THE TWO OF YOU
ARE GOING TO MEGALONIA,

00:03:06.486 --> 00:03:09.920
BUT WINNING THE CHAMPIONSHIP
WON'T BE THE ENDGAME.

00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:12.653
WHAT'S THE BEST THING
YOU AND THE KID CAN DO?

00:03:12.653 --> 00:03:14.953
WHAT WOULD THE SMART MOVE BE?

00:03:14.953 --> 00:03:17.820
THINK. TELL ME
WHAT COMES TO MIND, NANBU.

00:03:17.820 --> 00:03:19.520
( Nanbu gasping )

00:03:20.753 --> 00:03:23.153
♪

00:03:27.286 --> 00:03:29.086
( chuckles )

00:03:29.086 --> 00:03:31.086
( Fujimaki exhales )

00:03:31.086 --> 00:03:35.020
"BUT YOU'LL STING ME, WON'T YOU?
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO."

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:36.820
"NO, I WOULD NEVER DO THAT."

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:39.886
"BECAUSE IF YOU DIE
HALFWAY ACROSS,

00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:43.120
I'LL DROWN
AND DIE RIGHT BESIDE YOU."

00:03:44.753 --> 00:03:47.553
Nanbu: SO, AFTER SOME THOUGHT,
I KNEW WHAT TO DO.

00:03:47.553 --> 00:03:49.953
WE COULD THROW A FIGHT
AT MEGALONIA,

00:03:49.953 --> 00:03:51.320
THE BIGGEST FIXED MATCH EVER.

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:52.453
Joe: HUH?

00:03:52.453 --> 00:03:54.620
Nanbu: AND OUR ONLY CHANCE
TO PULL IT OFF

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:57.520
WOULD BE YOUR OPENER,
THE ONE AGAINST BURROUGHS.

00:03:57.520 --> 00:04:00.120
FUJIMAKI WILL BE RUNNING
THE BETS FOR THE EVENT.

00:04:00.120 --> 00:04:02.760
THAT'LL BE TONS OF CASH.
LOOK, THERE'S NO OTHER WAY

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:04.060
FOR US TO BE FREE
FROM EVERYTHING‐‐

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:07.493
Joe: YOU NEVER BELIEVED IN ME,
DID YOU, OLD MAN?

00:04:07.493 --> 00:04:09.626
Nanbu: NO, THAT'S NOT IT.
THE MORE YOU WON,

00:04:09.626 --> 00:04:12.893
THE MORE I STARTED TO THINK
THAT YOU ACTUALLY HAD A SHOT.

00:04:12.893 --> 00:04:15.093
BUT NOT ANYMORE.
NOW IT'S TOO DAMN LATE.

00:04:15.093 --> 00:04:18.093
I HAD NO OTHER WAY
OF GETTING THAT FAKE I. D.

00:04:18.093 --> 00:04:20.126
Y‐YOU GOTTA BELIEVE ME!

00:04:20.126 --> 00:04:23.993
JOE, SERIOUSLY, I GUARANTEE
THAT YOUR SKILLS ARE REAL.

00:04:23.993 --> 00:04:25.293
( Joe sighs )

00:04:25.293 --> 00:04:27.093
Nanbu: AND THIS
ISN'T THE END, OKAY?

00:04:27.093 --> 00:04:28.526
THINK OF IT AS A DETOUR

00:04:28.526 --> 00:04:30.626
ON THE WAY
TO THE SAME DESTINATION. YEAH?

00:04:30.626 --> 00:04:35.093
OKAY, JOE? IN THE NEXT MATCH,
WE'RE BACK TO USING THIS.

00:04:35.093 --> 00:04:37.093
Joe: YOU ASSHOLE!

00:04:38.659 --> 00:04:40.760
Nanbu: HOLY SHIT, MY JAW!

00:04:40.760 --> 00:04:43.293
LOOK, YOU GOTTA
FACE THE FACTS, JOE.

00:04:43.293 --> 00:04:46.626
FUJIMAKI'S NOT EXACTLY THE KIND
OF GUY YOU CAN REASON WITH.

00:04:46.626 --> 00:04:49.226
I DID ALL THIS, BECAUSE I
DIDN'T WANT YOU TO END UP‐‐

00:04:49.226 --> 00:04:51.860
Joe: YOU WERE ONLY WORRIED
ABOUT YOURSELF.

00:04:51.860 --> 00:04:53.126
Nanbu: YOU LITTLE PRICK!

00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:54.760
WHERE'S THE GRATITUDE, HUH?!

00:04:54.760 --> 00:04:56.660
WHO DO YOU THINK
MADE IT POSSIBLE

00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:59.460
FOR A STREET MUTT LIKE YOU
TO GET THIS FAR?!

00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:01.500
FRAUDS LIKE YOU AND ME,

00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:04.500
WE CAN NEVER BE LEGIT,
EVEN IF WE DIE TRYING.

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:07.900
( Joe chuckles )
ISN'T THAT JUST LIKE YOU, POPS?

00:05:07.900 --> 00:05:10.533
YOU DON'T HAVE
A LEGIT BONE IN YOUR BODY.

00:05:10.533 --> 00:05:13.166
‐ YOU'RE NOTHING BUT HOT AIR.
‐ Nanbu: HOLD ON.

00:05:13.166 --> 00:05:16.900
Joe: I WAS STUPID
FOR EVER THINKING OTHERWISE.

00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:19.400
Nanbu: JOE, WAIT UP!
WE'RE NOT DONE TALKING!

00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:20.900
Joe: I'M DONE WITH YOU.

00:05:27.833 --> 00:05:29.366
Sachio: TELL ME
IT'S A LIE, POPS!

00:05:29.366 --> 00:05:31.700
THE THREE OF US
ARE A TEAM, RIGHT?!

00:05:31.700 --> 00:05:34.033
WE'VE ALREADY MADE IT SO FAR!

00:05:34.033 --> 00:05:37.166
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO GO
ALL THE WAY IN MEGALONIA.

00:05:38.566 --> 00:05:39.766
SAY SOMETHING, DAMN IT!

00:05:39.766 --> 00:05:41.266
Nanbu: SHUT UP!

00:05:41.266 --> 00:05:42.666
THERE'S A TIME
FOR CHASING DREAMS,

00:05:42.666 --> 00:05:45.100
AND THIS AIN'T IT,
YOU STUPID BRAT!

00:05:47.766 --> 00:05:49.300
( Sachio gasps )

00:05:57.466 --> 00:05:59.900
Fujimaki: THAT'S THE THING
ABOUT SWEET DREAMS.

00:05:59.900 --> 00:06:02.206
IT ALWAYS HURTS
WHEN YOU WAKE UP.

00:06:02.206 --> 00:06:04.940
THIS IS WHAT IT
ALL COMES DOWN TO.

00:06:04.940 --> 00:06:07.740
IF YOU DON'T DELIVER
ON OUR DEAL, NANBU,

00:06:07.740 --> 00:06:10.140
YOU WON'T BE
THE ONLY ONE TO DIE.

00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:12.773
THE BOTH OF THEM WILL, TOO.

00:06:14.606 --> 00:06:16.373
♪

00:06:33.373 --> 00:06:36.406
( Joe screams )

00:06:41.240 --> 00:06:44.173
Iglesias: YURI ES EL GRAN
CAMPE ÓN SIN NINGUNA DUDA.

00:06:44.173 --> 00:06:47.606
POR ESO ME PONGO TRISTE CUANDO
ÉL SECAE EN EL CENTRO DE RING.

00:06:47.606 --> 00:06:49.273
PERO NO HAY OTRO REMEDIO.

00:06:49.273 --> 00:06:54.006
SOLAMENTE LOS M ÁS SOBREVIVEN.
AS Í ES MEGALOBOX.

00:06:54.006 --> 00:06:56.440
Moderator: AND NOW A WORD
FROM MR. BURROUGHS.

00:06:56.440 --> 00:06:57.906
( Burroughs scoffs )

00:06:57.906 --> 00:06:59.873
LOOKS LIKE
THE LITTLE PUNK IS A NO‐SHOW.

00:06:59.873 --> 00:07:02.813
HOPEFULLY, HE'LL BE HERE
FOR THE MATCH.

00:07:02.813 --> 00:07:04.013
( reporters laugh )

00:07:04.013 --> 00:07:05.846
Moderator: NOW,
THE SECOND MATCH OF MEGALONIA

00:07:05.846 --> 00:07:08.380
IS GOING TO BE BURROUGHS
VERSUS "GEARLESS" JOE,

00:07:08.380 --> 00:07:09.746
WHO, AS YOU CAN SEE,

00:07:09.746 --> 00:07:10.846
HASN'T ATTENDED
TODAY'S PRESS CONFERENCE.

00:07:10.846 --> 00:07:12.246
Asamoto:
THERE'S BEEN NO WORD YET

00:07:12.246 --> 00:07:14.180
FROM TEAM NOWHERE,
MS. SHIRATO.

00:07:14.180 --> 00:07:15.880
Moderator: WE CERTAINLY HOPE
THERE'S NO TROUBLE.

00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:19.146
Reporter: AND NOW
A QUESTION FOR THE CHAMPION.

00:07:19.146 --> 00:07:21.446
YOU'VE BEEN
THE NUMBER ONE FAVORITE
TO WIN THE TOURNAMENT...

00:07:21.446 --> 00:07:23.646
Abuhachi: IT'S LIKE
SOMETHING OUT OF A DREAM, HUH?

00:07:23.646 --> 00:07:25.180
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S ONLY BEEN THREE MONTHS

00:07:25.180 --> 00:07:28.246
SINCE YOU BROUGHT IN
THAT CLUNKY, BROKE‐DOWN GEAR.

00:07:28.246 --> 00:07:29.713
LOOK WHERE YOU ARE NOW.

00:07:29.713 --> 00:07:32.080
Yuri: ...INTENDING TO WIN.
END OF STORY.

00:07:32.080 --> 00:07:33.846
‐ ( Joe sighs )
‐ Iglesias: ACUERDO.

00:07:33.846 --> 00:07:35.780
ESA ES LA ACTITUD DE TODOS
LOS QUE SON CAMPEONES.

00:07:35.780 --> 00:07:37.680
Abuhachi: HMM.

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:41.680
I DIDN'T THINK I'D EVER SEE
YOU HERE AGAIN, TO BE HONEST.

00:07:41.680 --> 00:07:43.680
DID YOU GET LOST OR SOMETHING?

00:07:44.746 --> 00:07:46.213
Joe: YEAH.

00:07:46.213 --> 00:07:48.680
Reporter: BE SURE TO TUNE IN
WHEN WE GO LIVE AT MEGALONIA.

00:07:51.813 --> 00:07:53.680
( footsteps )

00:07:55.446 --> 00:07:56.813
( Sachio sighs )

00:07:56.813 --> 00:07:58.746
Nanbu: YOU WORRIED
THE HELL OUT OF ME.

00:07:58.746 --> 00:08:01.586
HERE. COME ON.
WE'RE GOING FOR A RIDE.

00:08:01.586 --> 00:08:03.886
( Sachio sighs ) HMPH.

00:08:03.886 --> 00:08:05.986
Nanbu: STOP BEING
SUCH A STUBBORN LITTLE ASS.

00:08:05.986 --> 00:08:08.020
YOU WANT FUJIMAKI
TO MAKE YOU INTO SOUP?

00:08:08.020 --> 00:08:09.586
Sachio: IT DOESN'T
MATTER ANYMORE, POPS!

00:08:09.586 --> 00:08:11.320
JOE SAID WE'RE FINISHED!

00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:12.820
SO MUCH FOR GOING ALL THE WAY.

00:08:12.820 --> 00:08:14.953
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU USED HIM LIKE THAT.

00:08:14.953 --> 00:08:17.220
Nanbu: YOU USED HIM, TOO, KID.

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:18.886
‐ Sachio: GIVE THAT BACK!
‐ Nanbu: AH!

00:08:18.886 --> 00:08:21.953
YOU THOUGHT JOE MAKING IT IN
TO MEGALONIA AND THEN WINNING IT

00:08:21.953 --> 00:08:24.420
WOULD BE REVENGE
FOR YOUR OLD MAN, DIDN'T YOU?

00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:25.420
( Sachio grunts )

00:08:25.420 --> 00:08:27.420
HOW‐‐HOW DID YOU‐‐

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:30.586
Nanbu: THAT GUY MIZUHARA,
YOU REMEMBER HIM?

00:08:30.586 --> 00:08:33.120
SOMETHING ABOUT HOW HE LOOKED
AT YOU GRABBED MY ATTENTION.

00:08:35.353 --> 00:08:38.186
SO TELL ME, YOU KNOW THAT KID?

00:08:38.186 --> 00:08:40.753
Koichi: THERE WAS THIS GUY
I WORKED WITH BACK AT SHIRATO

00:08:40.753 --> 00:08:42.720
WHO USED TO SHOW ME
PICTURES OF HIS KID,

00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:45.553
BRAGGING ABOUT HIS SON
CONSTANTLY.

00:08:45.553 --> 00:08:48.553
Nanbu: OH, YEAH?
WHAT WAS THIS FELLA LIKE?

00:08:49.886 --> 00:08:51.586
Koichi: HE WAS
A FREELANCE ENGINEER,

00:08:51.586 --> 00:08:53.020
SAME AS ME.
WE WEREN'T VERY CLOSE.

00:08:53.020 --> 00:08:56.686
I GUESS HE WAS TOO TALENTED,
POOR S. O. B.

00:08:56.686 --> 00:08:58.753
YEARS OF RESEARCH DATA
HE'D PILED UP,

00:08:58.753 --> 00:09:01.393
SHIRATO SWOOPED IN
AND STOLE IT FROM HIM.

00:09:01.393 --> 00:09:03.026
Nanbu: SO WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT GUY?

00:09:03.026 --> 00:09:05.260
( Koichi exhales )

00:09:05.260 --> 00:09:06.393
HMM.

00:09:06.393 --> 00:09:09.493
THE POOR BASTARD IS DEAD NOW...

00:09:09.493 --> 00:09:11.793
LEAVING HIS WIFE
AND KID BEHIND.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:15.626
Sachio: YEAH, IT'S TRUE.

00:09:15.626 --> 00:09:17.460
MY DAD WAS‐‐

00:09:17.460 --> 00:09:19.593
HE WAS KILLED BY SHIRATO.

00:09:19.593 --> 00:09:21.260
Nanbu: AND WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR MOTHER?

00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:23.760
Sachio: SHE GOT SICK,
DIED A YEAR LATER.

00:09:25.093 --> 00:09:28.593
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING,
BUT I BET JOE COULD.

00:09:28.593 --> 00:09:32.393
I BET HE COULD BEAT ALL THOSE
STUPID JERKS OVER AT SHIRATO,

00:09:32.393 --> 00:09:35.493
BUT NOW,
BECAUSE OF WHAT YOU DID...

00:09:37.826 --> 00:09:39.326
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?!

00:09:39.326 --> 00:09:41.160
HEY, DON'T RUN AWAY FROM ME!

00:09:42.260 --> 00:09:44.160
( overlapping chatter )

00:09:53.693 --> 00:09:55.626
WAIT. IS THIS...

00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:58.226
Nanbu: GO AND GET YOUR REVENGE.

00:09:58.226 --> 00:09:59.160
Sachio: HUH?

00:10:00.733 --> 00:10:02.400
Nanbu: SEE, YOU AND ME,

00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:04.500
WE JUST HAPPENED TO GET
ON THE SAME BOAT

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:07.500
CHASING DOWN
OUR OWN GOALS AND DREAMS.

00:10:07.500 --> 00:10:09.066
THAT'S WHY NEITHER JOE
NOR I EVER ASKED YOU

00:10:09.066 --> 00:10:12.200
ABOUT WHY YOU JOINED UP
WITH US IN THE FIRST PLACE.

00:10:12.200 --> 00:10:14.900
BUT NOW, THINGS HAVE CHANGED.

00:10:14.900 --> 00:10:17.000
EVERYTHING'S DIFFERENT
FROM BACK WHEN WE STARTED.

00:10:21.800 --> 00:10:23.900
YOU WANNA TAKE SHIRATO DOWN,
RIGHT?

00:10:23.900 --> 00:10:27.133
THIS IS ALL I CAN DO
FOR YOU NOW, KID.

00:10:27.133 --> 00:10:29.733
‐ THE REST IS UP TO YOU.
‐ Woman: ABSOLUTELY.
ANY TIME YOU LIKE.

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:31.733
( Sachio gasps )

00:10:38.866 --> 00:10:41.766
Girl: I'M LEARNING SO MUCH
AT SCHOOL RIGHT NOW!

00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:42.800
♪

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:54.533
Sachio: MY REVENGE...

00:10:54.533 --> 00:10:57.066
WILL BE GETTING TO THE TOP
WITH JOE.

00:10:58.633 --> 00:11:00.973
Nanbu: YOU AND I
BET EVERYTHING ON HIM.

00:11:00.973 --> 00:11:05.273
THE THING IS, HE'S THE ONE
WHO DECIDES HOW THIS PLAYS OUT.

00:11:05.273 --> 00:11:08.640
( bag thumping )

00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:11.406
AND YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO
THAT THERE'S NO TELLING

00:11:11.406 --> 00:11:13.340
WHAT THAT KID'S UP TO
UNTIL HE DOES IT.

00:11:14.806 --> 00:11:17.006
Sachio: "GEARLESS" JOE
WOULD NEVER THROW A MATCH.

00:11:17.006 --> 00:11:18.540
THAT'S FOR SURE.

00:11:18.540 --> 00:11:20.873
Nanbu: THEN YOU NEED TO HIDE
AND STAY LOW.

00:11:20.873 --> 00:11:21.540
Sachio: HUH?

00:11:21.540 --> 00:11:23.473
Nanbu: I DOUBT EVEN FUJIMAKI

00:11:23.473 --> 00:11:26.073
HAS ENOUGH MUSCLE
TO MESS WITH SHIRATO.

00:11:26.073 --> 00:11:27.506
( Sachio gasps )

00:11:27.506 --> 00:11:29.473
Nanbu: THIS IS
FOR JOE'S SAKE, TOO.

00:11:31.373 --> 00:11:33.440
Yukiko: FIRST YOU
INTERRUPT THE CEREMONY,

00:11:33.440 --> 00:11:35.640
THEN YOU MISS
THE PRESS CONFERENCE,

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:38.373
AND NOW YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE IN THIS CHILD?

00:11:38.373 --> 00:11:40.840
YOU'RE CERTAINLY BOLD,
IF NOTHING ELSE.

00:11:40.840 --> 00:11:44.106
Nanbu: IT'S ALL AS I
EXPLAINED TO YOU, I SWEAR.

00:11:44.106 --> 00:11:47.206
LOOK INTO HIS PAST, AND I'M SURE
YOU'LL CONFIRM EVERYTHING.

00:11:47.206 --> 00:11:48.606
I FIGURE WITH ALL THAT HAPPENED,

00:11:48.606 --> 00:11:50.473
YOU AT LEAST OWE HIM
A HELPING HAND...

00:11:51.973 --> 00:11:54.873
EVEN IF IT'S ONLY
UNTIL JOE'S MATCH IS OVER.

00:11:54.873 --> 00:11:58.040
Yukiko: LISTEN CLOSELY.
I AM NOT THE LEAST BIT HAPPY

00:11:58.040 --> 00:12:00.480
THAT YOU ALL
MADE IT IN TO MEGALONIA.

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:02.680
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOUR ENDGAME IS HERE,

00:12:02.680 --> 00:12:05.780
BUT DID YOU EVER CONSIDER
I MIGHT HAVE CONDITIONS?

00:12:05.780 --> 00:12:08.846
FOR INSTANCE, DEMANDING JOE'S
WITHDRAWAL FROM THE TOURNAMENT

00:12:08.846 --> 00:12:11.380
IN EXCHANGE
FOR TAKING IN THIS CHILD?

00:12:12.380 --> 00:12:13.546
( Nanbu chuckles )

00:12:13.546 --> 00:12:15.346
YOU WOULDN'T DO THAT.

00:12:16.213 --> 00:12:17.446
ALTHOUGH...

00:12:18.980 --> 00:12:20.813
THAT'S NOT A BAD IDEA.

00:12:20.813 --> 00:12:22.046
( Yukiko gasps )

00:12:28.913 --> 00:12:31.280
Nanbu: THIS IS THE LAST
YOU'LL HEAR FROM ME.

00:12:33.313 --> 00:12:35.280
HERE, KID. TAKE THIS.

00:12:35.280 --> 00:12:36.746
Sachio: UH...

00:12:36.746 --> 00:12:39.213
Nanbu: LOOK AFTER JOE FOR ME,
SACHIO, OKAY?

00:12:39.213 --> 00:12:40.913
( Sachio grunts )

00:12:40.913 --> 00:12:42.446
( sighs )

00:12:42.446 --> 00:12:44.413
BUT WHAT ABOUT YOU?

00:12:44.413 --> 00:12:46.213
Nanbu: SEE YOU, KID.

00:12:46.213 --> 00:12:48.380
( Joe panting )

00:12:56.346 --> 00:12:58.780
‐ ( Joe yells )
‐ ( chain rattles )

00:13:07.053 --> 00:13:08.953
♪

00:13:08.953 --> 00:13:11.853
Announcer: THE DAY WE'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR IS FINALLY HERE,

00:13:11.853 --> 00:13:15.620
THE BATTLE TO SEE WHO STANDS
AT THE SUMMIT OF MEGALO‐BOXING!

00:13:15.620 --> 00:13:18.553
WE'RE NEARING THE OPENING ROUND
OF MEGALONIA!

00:13:18.553 --> 00:13:21.753
TAKE A GOOD LOOK AT THIS CROWD.
THE ARENA'S AT CAPACITY!

00:13:21.753 --> 00:13:24.086
HERE ON THE VERGE
OF THIS HISTORIC SPORTING EVENT,

00:13:24.086 --> 00:13:27.853
THE ANTICIPATION AND EXCITEMENT
ARE HOTTER THAN EVER!

00:13:27.853 --> 00:13:29.820
Officer: I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE
WHAT YOU'VE PUT TOGETHER.

00:13:29.820 --> 00:13:31.853
‐ Yukiko: THANK YOU.
‐ Asamoto: MADAM PRESIDENT.

00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:33.353
Yukiko: PARDON ME.

00:13:33.353 --> 00:13:34.986
Officer: OF COURSE.

00:13:37.486 --> 00:13:39.453
Asamoto:
AFTER AN INTERNAL AUDIT,

00:13:39.453 --> 00:13:41.786
WE'VE DISCOVERED
THAT THE DESIGN DATA

00:13:41.786 --> 00:13:44.453
FOR KEY COMPONENTS
IN THE INTEGRATED GEAR

00:13:44.453 --> 00:13:46.686
WERE PROCURED
IN AN UNORTHODOX MANNER.

00:13:46.686 --> 00:13:49.820
IT SEEMS CERTAIN
THAT THE ORIGINAL DEVELOPER

00:13:49.820 --> 00:13:53.420
OF THE IMMUNOSUPPRESSANT
MECHANISM WAS THE BOY'S FATHER.

00:13:59.826 --> 00:14:02.760
( Sachio sighs )

00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:05.193
♪

00:14:22.826 --> 00:14:24.493
Ring announcer:
OVER IN THE EAST CORNER,

00:14:24.493 --> 00:14:28.160
THE SECOND‐RANKED I. M. A. BOXER,

00:14:28.160 --> 00:14:30.593
WITH THE TRES FAMILIAS,

00:14:30.593 --> 00:14:35.993
PEPE "THE SPIDER" IGLESIAS!

00:14:35.993 --> 00:14:37.726
( crowd cheering )

00:14:41.126 --> 00:14:42.493
Announcer: AND THERE HE IS!

00:14:42.493 --> 00:14:44.360
THE BIG QUESTION FOR THIS MATCH

00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:46.560
IS CAN THE VICIOUS
SPIDER FROM MEXICO

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:48.493
LAY THE CHAMP OUT
HERE IN THE RING OF MEGALONIA,

00:14:48.493 --> 00:14:51.360
JUST AS HE CLAIMED HE WOULD
IN THE PRESS CONFERENCE?

00:14:51.360 --> 00:14:52.626
( Iglesias grunting )

00:14:52.626 --> 00:14:54.226
Ring announcer:
AND NOW JOINING US

00:14:54.226 --> 00:14:55.993
IN THE WEST CORNER IS...

00:14:55.993 --> 00:14:58.593
♪

00:15:15.700 --> 00:15:19.133
THE NUMBER‐ONE‐RANKED
I. M. A. BOXER,

00:15:19.133 --> 00:15:21.100
WITH TEAM SHIRATO,

00:15:21.100 --> 00:15:25.000
THE KING OF THE RING, YURI!

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.566
( crowd cheering )

00:15:31.733 --> 00:15:34.066
Announcer:
THE IMPLACABLE CHAMPION, YURI!

00:15:34.066 --> 00:15:35.600
SPORTING THE INTEGRATED GEAR

00:15:35.600 --> 00:15:37.700
THAT HAS BECOME
SHIRATO'S CALLING CARD,

00:15:37.700 --> 00:15:40.400
IT'S BECOME AS INTERTWINED
WITH THIS BRILLIANT BOXER'S NAME

00:15:40.400 --> 00:15:42.433
AS MUCH AS HIS BODY,
ALLOWING HIM TO FEND OFF

00:15:42.433 --> 00:15:44.566
EVERY CLAIM ON HIS TITLE SO FAR!

00:15:44.566 --> 00:15:46.366
Yukiko: OUR GEAR WAS DEVELOPED

00:15:46.366 --> 00:15:49.033
THANKS TO THE SACRIFICES
OF ALL INVOLVED.

00:15:49.033 --> 00:15:52.700
AS SUCH, WE CONSIDER VICTORY
TO BE AN OBLIGATION.

00:15:52.700 --> 00:15:53.366
Officer: MM.

00:15:53.366 --> 00:15:54.733
Yukiko: DIRECTOR ASAMOTO.

00:15:54.733 --> 00:15:55.766
Asamoto: MA'AM?

00:15:55.766 --> 00:15:57.533
Yukiko: ASSEMBLE A LIST
OF THOSE INVOLVED

00:15:57.533 --> 00:15:59.366
IN THE IRREGULARITY
YOU MENTIONED.

00:15:59.366 --> 00:16:01.406
WE'LL MAKE SURE THAT THEY'RE
PROPERLY DEALT WITH.

00:16:01.406 --> 00:16:03.240
Asamoto: UNDERSTOOD, MA'AM.

00:16:05.173 --> 00:16:07.240
( crowd cheering )

00:16:13.173 --> 00:16:15.573
( overlapping chatter )

00:16:18.206 --> 00:16:19.840
( horn blows )

00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:21.440
Man: GO, YURI!

00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:23.540
‐ Man #2: iPEPE! iM ÁTALO!
‐ Announcer: THE MATCH BEGINS,

00:16:23.540 --> 00:16:26.040
AND PEPE GOES STRAIGHT
INTO AN AGGRESSIVE ATTACK!

00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:27.706
Commentator:
HE'S GOT THAT LONG REACH

00:16:27.706 --> 00:16:30.406
AND A DISTINCT POSTURE THAT
MAKES IT HARD TO GET INSIDE.

00:16:30.406 --> 00:16:33.673
COMBINE THAT WITH THE VARIETY
OF ATTACKS HE CAN PULL OFF,

00:16:33.673 --> 00:16:35.773
AND OVER TIME, HIS OPPONENTS
FIND THEY'RE UNABLE

00:16:35.773 --> 00:16:39.773
TO FIGHT BACK EFFECTIVELY,
LIKE THEY'RE CAUGHT IN HIS WEB.

00:16:39.773 --> 00:16:41.906
THAT'S HOW HE GOT
THE NICKNAME "SPIDER."

00:16:41.906 --> 00:16:43.706
( Iglesias grunting )

00:16:49.040 --> 00:16:51.973
Announcer: NEITHER FIGHTER
IS GIVING AN INCH SO FAR.

00:16:51.973 --> 00:16:55.306
WILL THE TRADITIONAL YURI
BE ABLE TO OVERCOME

00:16:55.306 --> 00:16:57.873
PEPE'S UNCONVENTIONAL
FIGHTING STYLE?

00:16:57.873 --> 00:16:59.540
( horn blows )

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:01.580
AND THAT'S THE END
OF THE FIRST ROUND!

00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:04.380
THINGS ARE ALREADY
INCREDIBLY TENSE!

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:05.780
Commentator:
MOST LIKELY, ONE OF THESE MEN

00:17:05.780 --> 00:17:08.713
WILL BE GOING ON THE OFFENSIVE
IN THE NEXT ROUND.

00:17:10.013 --> 00:17:12.046
( horn blows )

00:17:12.046 --> 00:17:14.546
♪

00:17:26.080 --> 00:17:27.446
( Yuri gasps )

00:17:30.280 --> 00:17:33.346
Announcer: AH! PEPE SEEMS
TO HAVE FINALLY CAUGHT YURI,

00:17:33.346 --> 00:17:35.380
THE FIRST HIT
OF THE MATCH TO LAND!

00:17:35.380 --> 00:17:37.580
Iglesias:
TE VOY A MATAR, CAMPE ÓN.

00:17:38.880 --> 00:17:39.580
( Yuri chuckles )

00:17:41.746 --> 00:17:42.546
( Joe growls )

00:18:03.186 --> 00:18:05.186
Referee: HE'S DOWN!

00:18:05.186 --> 00:18:07.153
Computer: 1, 2...

00:18:07.153 --> 00:18:09.886
Announcer: WH‐WHAT IN THE WORLD
HAPPENED UP THERE?!

00:18:09.886 --> 00:18:13.186
IT WAS ALL SO FAST. THE WAY
THAT PEPE DROPPED TO THE MAT,

00:18:13.186 --> 00:18:15.020
YOU'D THINK HE'D BEEN SHOT
OR SOMETHING!

00:18:15.020 --> 00:18:16.420
Commentator: IT WAS A LEFT HOOK,

00:18:16.420 --> 00:18:18.353
AND, UNFORTUNATELY FOR PEPE,

00:18:18.353 --> 00:18:20.420
I DON'T THINK
HE EVER SAW IT COMING.

00:18:20.420 --> 00:18:22.720
‐ Computer: 10.
‐ ( horn blows )

00:18:22.720 --> 00:18:25.720
Referee: WITH A K. O. AT 2:10
INTO THE SECOND ROUND,

00:18:25.720 --> 00:18:30.953
THE WINNER,
WITH TEAM SHIRATO, IS YURI!

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:49.086
( dog whimpering )

00:18:49.086 --> 00:18:50.053
Joe: HUH?

00:18:50.053 --> 00:18:52.120
HEY THERE, BOY.

00:18:52.120 --> 00:18:53.853
WHERE'D YOU COME FROM?

00:18:53.853 --> 00:18:55.386
( man whistles )

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:02.626
( Yuri grunts )

00:19:08.193 --> 00:19:10.093
Joe: SO, HE'S YOURS?

00:19:10.093 --> 00:19:12.326
Yuri: YEAH. IT'S ODD, THOUGH.

00:19:12.326 --> 00:19:14.893
HE USUALLY
DOESN'T LIKE STRANGERS.

00:19:14.893 --> 00:19:17.460
Joe: GOTTA SAY,
THAT WAS A HELL OF A HOOK.

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:19.726
I ACTUALLY FELT
KIND OF BAD FOR PEPE.

00:19:19.726 --> 00:19:21.460
THAT GUY NEVER HAD A CHANCE.

00:19:21.460 --> 00:19:23.560
Yuri: WHEN YOU
STEP INTO THE RING,

00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:26.826
YOU EITHER WIN OR LOSE.
THERE'S NOTHING ELSE.

00:19:26.826 --> 00:19:28.760
EVERYONE'S EQUAL.

00:19:28.760 --> 00:19:29.893
( Joe chuckles )

00:19:32.826 --> 00:19:36.260
Yuri: WHY AREN'T YOU USING GEAR?

00:19:36.260 --> 00:19:40.460
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY YOU
INSIST ON FIGHTING WITHOUT IT.

00:19:40.460 --> 00:19:42.360
Joe: AT FIRST,
IT WAS JUST A GAMBLE

00:19:42.360 --> 00:19:46.360
TO GET MY NAME OUT THERE,
BUT NOW IT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

00:19:46.360 --> 00:19:48.193
( chuckles )

00:19:49.360 --> 00:19:51.493
EVERY TIME I GET IN THE RING,

00:19:51.493 --> 00:19:53.826
I'M BETTING MY LIFE
ON WHAT MY FISTS CAN DO.

00:19:53.826 --> 00:19:56.293
IT'S SCARY AS HELL, NO DOUBT,

00:19:56.293 --> 00:19:58.593
BUT IT'S SO FUN,
I CAN BARELY STAND IT.

00:20:02.100 --> 00:20:04.866
I WANNA FIGHT YOU
IN A REAL MATCH,

00:20:04.866 --> 00:20:06.800
PURE AND SIMPLE.

00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:08.100
I THINK, AGAINST YOU,

00:20:08.100 --> 00:20:10.833
I'D GO FURTHER
THAN I'VE EVER GONE BEFORE.

00:20:10.833 --> 00:20:11.866
Yuri: EH...

00:20:11.866 --> 00:20:13.566
Joe: AND WHAT ABOUT YOU?

00:20:13.566 --> 00:20:15.466
WHAT ARE YOU FIGHTING FOR?

00:20:17.933 --> 00:20:19.633
Yuri: A DREAM.

00:20:19.633 --> 00:20:20.633
Joe: HUH?

00:20:20.633 --> 00:20:22.866
Yuri: THERE WAS SOMEONE
WHO BELIEVED IN ME.

00:20:22.866 --> 00:20:24.900
SHE HAD FAITH IN ME
WHEN I WAS NOTHING

00:20:24.900 --> 00:20:26.966
AND BROUGHT ME THIS FAR.

00:20:26.966 --> 00:20:28.666
HER DREAM IS WHY.

00:20:28.666 --> 00:20:30.100
( Joe sighs )

00:20:30.100 --> 00:20:32.233
( Nanbu groaning )

00:20:40.100 --> 00:20:41.866
SWEET DREAMS, HUH?

00:20:41.866 --> 00:20:42.833
( chuckles )

00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:47.000
Fujimaki: HAVE YOU DISCUSSED
THINGS WITH YOUR PARTNER?

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:49.166
( Nanbu laughs )
YOU BET I HAVE.

00:20:49.166 --> 00:20:52.233
AND THE THOUGHT OF FINALLY BEING
OUT FROM UNDERNEATH THIS DEBT

00:20:52.233 --> 00:20:55.200
REQUIRES A CELEBRATORY DRINK.
YOU UNDERSTAND.

00:20:55.200 --> 00:20:57.233
Fujimaki: YOU TRULY
ARE A SCORPION.

00:20:57.233 --> 00:20:59.240
HERE. LET'S DRINK TO THAT.

00:20:59.240 --> 00:21:00.206
Nanbu: HUH?

00:21:01.773 --> 00:21:04.140
Fujimaki:
NEVER HEARD THAT STORY?

00:21:04.140 --> 00:21:06.106
THERE'S THIS SCORPION, SEE,

00:21:06.106 --> 00:21:09.373
AND THERE'S THIS RIVER
HE WANTS TO CROSS.

00:21:09.373 --> 00:21:12.773
PROBLEM IS,
SCORPIONS CAN'T SWIM,

00:21:12.773 --> 00:21:16.206
SO THE SCORPION ASKS A FROG
THAT HAPPENS TO BE BY THE RIVER

00:21:16.206 --> 00:21:18.073
IF HE'D GIVE HIM A RIDE
ON HIS BACK

00:21:18.073 --> 00:21:20.273
SO HE CAN GET ACROSS SAFELY.

00:21:20.273 --> 00:21:22.840
THE FROG SAYS TO THE SCORPION,

00:21:22.840 --> 00:21:25.573
"I DON'T KNOW.
YOU'LL STING ME, WON'T YOU?"

00:21:25.573 --> 00:21:29.206
THE SCORPION RESPONDS,
"I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

00:21:29.206 --> 00:21:31.106
IT WOULDN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

00:21:31.106 --> 00:21:34.640
IF YOU WERE TO DIE
HALFWAY ACROSS, I'D DROWN."

00:21:34.640 --> 00:21:37.906
THE FROG PONDERS THIS
FOR A MOMENT AND IS CONVINCED,

00:21:37.906 --> 00:21:40.106
SO HE KINDLY LETS THE SCORPION
ONTO HIS BACK

00:21:40.106 --> 00:21:41.773
AND STARTS TO CROSS THE RIVER.

00:21:41.773 --> 00:21:47.440
BUT WHILE THEY'RE IN THE WATER,
THE SCORPION STINGS THE FROG.

00:21:47.440 --> 00:21:49.840
AS HE'S LOSING CONSCIOUSNESS,
THE FROG SAYS,

00:21:49.840 --> 00:21:53.673
"YOU TOLD ME YOU WOULDN'T
STING ME. NOW WE'LL BOTH DIE."

00:21:53.673 --> 00:21:55.906
AND AS THEY SANK
BENEATH THE WATER,

00:21:55.906 --> 00:21:57.606
THE SCORPION TELLS HIM...

00:21:57.606 --> 00:21:59.780
Nanbu: "I JUST COULDN'T HELP IT.

00:21:59.780 --> 00:22:03.046
IT'S SIMPLY THE NATURE
OF A SCORPION TO STING."

00:22:03.046 --> 00:22:04.813
♪

